      • apply

        void apply(RDFList.ApplyFn fn)
    throws ReadDeniedException,
           AuthenticationRequiredException
        Uses the security settings for the application of the function calls. Thus if the function reads data the Read must be allowed, etc.
        Specified by:
        apply in interface RDFList
        Throws:
        ReadDeniedException - graph Read or other permissions are not met
        AuthenticationRequiredException - if user is not authenticated and is required to be.
        Required graph permissions:
        Read
        Required triple permissions:
        Read (to be included in the calculation), other permissions required by the function.

      • apply

        void apply(Set<SecurityEvaluator.Action> constraints,
           RDFList.ApplyFn fn)
    throws ReadDeniedException,
           AuthenticationRequiredException
        This method is intended to provide the capabilities to apply functions that need to do more than read the graph. If the user does not have constraints access to the item in the list the item is not included in the function.
        Parameters:
        constraints - The permissions the user must have on the items in the list.
        fn - The function to apply.
        Throws:
        ReadDeniedException
        AuthenticationRequiredException - if user is not authenticated and is required to be.
        Required graph permissions:
        Read
        Required triple permissions:
        Read and constraints

      • reduce

        Object reduce(Set<SecurityEvaluator.Action> requiredActions,
              RDFList.ReduceFn fn,
              Object initial)
       throws ReadDeniedException,
              EmptyListException,
              ListIndexException,
              InvalidListException,
              AuthenticationRequiredException
        Only readable triples will be passed to the function. In addition, only triples that pass the requiredActions tests will be passed to the function.
        Parameters:
        requiredActions - The set of permission (in addition to Read) that the user must have
        fn - The reduction function
        initial - The initial state for the ruduce value.

        EmptyListException
